text.p: These are the leading stories in the Algerian press on Saturday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.
- Maghreb-Europe gas pipeline to be inaugurated on Saturday.
- Angola and Algeria agree to develop cooperation.
- A network of Algerian GIA radical Islamists dismantled in Italy.
- Return of German businessmen to the Algerian market.
- Algerian political parties explain their points of view before the constitutional referendum on November 28.
- Opposition leader Hocine Ait Ahmed says Front of Socialist Forces will participate in the elections.
